      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, \"interpreted the text as a dynamic document\" sounds like a contradiction though. If the text is dynamic, then it isn't really about the \"original\" meaning anymore, right? Isn't the whole point of originalism to prevent judges from just deciding what they think is \"contemporary\" and calling it law? It seems like you're saying the Court can just redefine the words to fit modern needs and still claim they're being faithful to the text, which sounds like the definition of judicial activism to me.",
